The high-temperature SCoeff in NaxCoO2 can be expressed by Koshibae’s equation [85, 86] for strongly correlated materials, which itself is a modified form of Heikes formula [87, 88]:11SCoeffT→∞=-kBelngCo3+gCo4+x1-x.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
